<li id="cite_note-48"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48" title="">^</a></b> Carl Braun's thirty causes appear in his Lehrbuch der Geburtshülfe (Vienna: Braumüller, 1857), p. 914. In the first of these, published in 1855, he mentions Semmelweis in connection with his discussion of cause number 28, cadaverous poisoning. In the later version, however, although he discusses the same cause in the same terms, all references to Semmelweis have been dropped. (Note by translator Carter in footnote 105 p34 in Semmelweis (1861)</li>
