<li id="cite_note-51"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLevy1848">Levy, Karl Edouard Marius (1848). "De nyeste Forsög i Födselsstiftelsen i Wien til Oplysning om Barselfeberens Aetiologie". <i>Hospitals-Meddelelser</i> <b>1</b>: 199–211.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=De+nyeste+Fors%C3%B6g+i+F%C3%B6dselsstiftelsen+i+Wien+til+Oplysning+om+Barselfeberens+Aetiologie&amp;rft.jtitle=Hospitals-Meddelelser&amp;rft.aulast=Levy&amp;rft.aufirst=Karl+Edouard+Marius&amp;rft.au=Levy%2C+Karl+Edouard+Marius&amp;rft.date=1848&amp;rft.volume=1&amp;rft.pages=199%E2%80%93211&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ignaz_Semmelweis"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (alternative spelling <a href="/wiki/Carl_Edvard_Marius_Levy" title="Carl Edvard Marius Levy">Carl Edvard Marius Levy</a>) quoted in Semmelweis (1861) p180-181</li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52" title="">^</a></b> Note by Carter (translator) footnote 17 in Semmelweis (1861) p183</li>
<li id="cite_note-SemmelBC-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-SemmelBC_53-0" title="">^</a></b> "Ignaz Philipp Semmelweis - Britannica Concise" (history), Imre Zoltán, <i>Britannica Concise</i>, 2006, webpage: <a href="http://concise.britannica.com/ebc/article-9066723/Semmelweis" class="external text" title="http://concise.britannica.com/ebc/article-9066723/Semmelweis" rel="nofollow">CBrit-Semmelweis</a>: birthname, doctorate 1844, objections of superiors, mortality 18.27 to 1.27 percent, fired for politics of 1848 rebellion, his 1861 book <i>Die Ätiologie</i>, pathologist <a href="/wiki/Rudolf_Virchow" title="Rudolf Virchow">Rudolf Virchow</a> rejected his doctrine.</li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Rudolf_Virchow" title="Rudolf Virchow">Rudolf Virchow</a>, professor of pathological anatomy, a scientist of the highest authority of his age. His father-in-law was the president of the Obstetrical Society of Berlin, and he was known for being in good relationship with <a href="/wiki/Franz_Kiwisch_von_Rotterau" title="Franz Kiwisch von Rotterau">Franz Kiwisch von Rotterau</a>. Virchow’s great authority in medical circles potently contributed to the lack of recognition of the Semmelweis doctrine for a long time. <cite style="font-style:normal">Hauzman, Erik E (2006). "<a href="http://www.ishm2006.hu/abstracts/files/ishmpaper_093.doc" class="external text" title="http://www.ishm2006.hu/abstracts/files/ishmpaper_093.doc" rel="nofollow"><i>Semmelweis and his German contemporaries</i></a>" (DOC).</cite> 40th International Congress on the History of Medicine, ISHM 2006<i>. <span class="reference-accessdate">Retrieved on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-06-05"><a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>-<a href="/wiki/June_5" title="June 5">06-05</a></span></span>.</i><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=proceeding&amp;rft.btitle=40th+International+Congress+on+the+History+of+Medicine%2C++ISHM+2006&amp;rft.atitle=%27%27Semmelweis+and+his+German+contemporaries&amp;rft.aulast=Hauzman&amp;rft.aufirst=Erik+E&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.place=Budapest%2C+Hungary%2C+August+26-30%2C+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ishm2006.hu%2Fabstracts%2Ffiles%2Fishmpaper_093.doc"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-55"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55" title="">^</a></b> e.g. by <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFNuland2003">Nuland, Sherwin B. (2003). <i>The Doctors' Plague: Germs, Childbed Fever and the Strange Story of Ignac Semmelweis</i>. W W Norton &amp; Co Ltd. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0393052990" class="internal">ISBN 0-393-05299-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Doctors%27+Plague%3A+Germs%2C+Childbed+Fever+and+the+Strange+Story+of+Ignac+Semmelweis&amp;rft.aulast=Nuland&amp;rft.aufirst=Sherwin+B.&amp;rft.au=Nuland%2C+Sherwin+B.&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=W+W+Norton+%26+Co+Ltd&amp;rft.isbn=0-393-05299-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ignaz_Semmelweis"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56" title="">^</a></b> Senmmelweis 1861:57</li>
<li id="cite_note-57"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57" title="">^</a></b> The 1862 open letter is available at Austrian literature online, Österreichische Nationalbibliothek <a href="http://www.literature.at/webinterface/library/ALO-BOOK_V01?objid=13184" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.literature.at/webinterface/library/ALO-BOOK_V01?objid=13184" rel="nofollow">[2]</a>. He repeatedly lashes out against <a href="/wiki/Carl_Braun_(obstetrician)" title="Carl Braun (obstetrician)">Carl Braun (obstetrician)</a> and <a href="/wiki/Friedrich_Wilhelm_Scanzoni_von_Lichtenfels" title="Friedrich Wilhelm Scanzoni von Lichtenfels">Friedrich Wilhelm Scanzoni von Lichtenfels</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-58"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58" title="">^</a></b> Semmelweis 1861:57</li>
<li id="cite_note-59"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59" title="">^</a></b> Carter 2005:73</li>
<li id="cite_note-60"><b><a href="#cite_ref-60" title="">^</a></b> Semmelweis 1861:41</li>
<li id="cite_note-61"><b><a href="#cite_ref-61" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal">Hauzman, Erik E (2006). "<a href="http://www.ishm2006.hu/abstracts/files/ishmpaper_093.doc" class="external text" title="http://www.ishm2006.hu/abstracts/files/ishmpaper_093.doc" rel="nofollow"><i>Semmelweis and his German contemporaries</i></a>" (DOC).</cite> 40th International Congress on the History of Medicine, ISHM 2006<i>. <span class="reference-accessdate">Retrieved on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-06-05"><a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>-<a href="/wiki/June_5" title="June 5">06-05</a></span></span>.</i><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=proceeding&amp;rft.btitle=40th+International+Congress+on+the+History+of+Medicine%2C++ISHM+2006&amp;rft.atitle=%27%27Semmelweis+and+his+German+contemporaries&amp;rft.aulast=Hauzman&amp;rft.aufirst=Erik+E&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.place=Budapest%2C+Hungary+August+26-30%2C+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ishm2006.hu%2Fabstracts%2Ffiles%2Fishmpaper_093.doc"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
